cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with machine learning models and their robustness to changes in data distribution, which is a common problem in practical settings. The specific application domain is bionic hand prostheses, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves transfer learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions learning vector quantization models, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
